  Tracker-ID placeholder convention (STE-66 / STE-80 / STE-122):
  When drafting FR or AC IDs in tracker mode, use the literal placeholder
  `<tracker-id>` until the tracker allocator assigns the real ID. Never
  guess the next sequential tracker number — the allocator decides, not
  the implementer. Substitute the real ID globally only after
  Provider.sync / importFromTracker returns it.

  AC IDs use `AC-<tracker-id>.<N>` in tracker mode (substituted by /spec-write
  via acPrefix(spec) — see STE-50 for AC-prefix derivation; mirrors STE-66's
  filename placeholder convention) or `AC-<short-ULID>.<N>` in mode: none
  (last 6 chars of the ULID random portion). Literal `AC-1.1` / `AC-2.1` /
  bare-digit-milestone-numbered shapes are rejected by /gate-check probe-15
  `guessed_tracker_id` and by /spec-write's post-write scan (STE-122
  AC-STE-122.3).

  See plugins/dev-process-toolkit/docs/spec-write-tracker-mode.md for the
  full rule and worked example. In mode: none, use the short-ULID tail
  instead; the placeholder convention does not apply.

  Example placeholder FR heading:
    ### <tracker-id>: <Title> {#<tracker-id>}
